  "response": "The abbreviations for degrees can vary depending on the context. Here are some common ones:\n\n1. **Celsius**: \u00b0C\n2. **Fahrenheit**: \u00b0F\n3. **Kelvin**: K\n4. **Degrees (general)**: \u00b0 (used before the unit, e.g., 25\u00b0)\n\nFor academic degrees, common abbreviations include:\n\n1. **Bachelor of Arts**: BA\n2. **Bachelor of Science**: BS\n3. **Master of Arts**: MA\n4. **Master of Science**: MS\n5. **Doctor of Philosophy**: PhD\n6. **Doctor of Medicine**: MD\n7. **Juris Doctor**: JD\n\nIf you're looking for a specific type of degree or context, please let me know!",
